b'"In the #newnormal, a lot of things changed, but not my belief that it\'s possible to experience and stay connected with nature despite being indoors. Thus came the idea of setting up a home fountain in my balcony. I purchased all the basics from the nearby stores like cement, paint, thermocol, water pump and started the activity. For me, it was a therapeutic experience and I\'ve realized that how pursuing something one loves offers a gateway to a more peaceful and happy place. This miniature fountain makes a perfect addition to my balcony where the sound of the water brings serenity and peace." Khusboo shares her experience on pursuing her Xfactor and explains how she found serenity in the very sounds of water. Check out our stories to see the fountain in action.:backhand_index_pointing_up:\n\n #MyXfactor #LifeAtInfy'

b'"The #newnormal has been a blessing in disguise for me. With plenty of time at hand, I hunkered down and started to wonder about aspects of life which we miss out between work, kids and other commitments. I knew I had to find a way to step out of the house safely and decided to try Mountain Biking. It was fun from the start \xe2\x80\x93 I tried small rides at first \xe2\x80\x93 neighborhood trails, greenway, etc. Eventually, the challenge of riding caught on." Neeraj talks about how mountain biking amidst lush green mountains and serene waters has kept him going during these times! #LifeAtInfy #MyXFactor'

b'Hi! I\xe2\x80\x99m Priyapravas Avasthi, part of Infosys\xe2\x80\x99 #LiveEnterprise. Have you ever thought of an organization as a living, breathing organism that adapts to changes? That credo is at the center of the work I do here. However, I am not going to be talking about work, but rather, give you a glimpse into who I am! :backhand_index_pointing_down:
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x80\xa2	Fan of Manga\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3
I\xe2\x80\x99m quite the fan of manga and you can find me wearing my comic-fandom on my sleeve - quite literally!  I enjoy popular #manga like #OnePiece and #DeathNote.
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x80\xa2	Passion for Wildlife and Wildlife films \xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3
I absolutely love Wildlife and Wildlife films, and a number of my friends are wildlife filmmakers: how lucky is that!? This is one passion that I love even more, and it melds into my work - and who I am! \xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x80\xa2	 Love Jam Bands\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3
Music, for me, speaks to my soul. I don\xe2\x80\x99t restrict genres, but I absolutely love the jam bands including Phish, Manic Street Preachers, and others. If I had to pick a favorite, it would definitely be the #GratefulDead.\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3
#MusicTrivia: The Dead were one of the first bands to be open to their fans recording music during live concerts. It\xe2\x80\x99s that sense of openness, community and collaboration that defines me. \xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x80\xa2	Humanity is an unbroken chain\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3
Humans are just one big community, all trying to do the best we can do in real-time, and the crux of our work lies in making that easier, because humanity\xe2\x80\x99s exactly that: an \xe2\x80\x9cUnbroken Chain\xe2\x80\x9d. \xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3
#HumansOfInfy #Infosys'

b'"I really enjoy painting. The colors at play on the canvas has always calmed me. Although, I must admit that I stopped doing it in the last few years and just watched my paints dry and brushes collect dust. With the luxury of being able to #workfromhome and so much time on hand, I had the urge to rekindle my lost hobby. My painting process is quite simple, I look for motivations around and simply bring that onto life on the Canvas." Catch a glimpse at how Aastha rekindled her passion for painting in our stories.:backhand_index_pointing_up: #NewNormal #MyXFactor #LifeAtInfy'
